notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (p. 1); later attribution to Bricci in ink (front flyleaf).
Notes in pencil in the hand of Henry Charles Lea (f. i).

msContents.summary: Treatise on penitence as a virtue and penance as a sacrament.

supportDesc.extent: 111 leaves : 273 x 199 (256 x 155) mm. bound to 280 x 198 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i + 111 + i leaves; 1-14, [ii], 15-200, 181-200; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by one hand with the exception of a few pages (p. 100-106) in a second hand.

origin.p: Written in Italy in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Henry Charles Lea (signature, dated 1891, front flyleaf); an unidentified library stamp includes the words Rome and des Français (p. 1).
